    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 3 @ 2023/2024",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Two resistors R₁ = 6Ω and R₂ = 2Ω in parallel are connected to R₃ = 4Ω in series. Find the equivalent resistance",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "4Ω",
        "5.5Ω",
        "2Ω",
        "8Ω"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "5.5Ω"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>The equivalent resistance of R₁ and R₂ in parallel is\\(\\frac{1}{R_p} =\\frac{1}{6} +\\frac{1}{2} =\\frac{1}{6} +\\frac{3}{6} =\\frac{4}{6}\\), so\\( R_p =\\frac{6}{4} = 1.5Ω\\). This is in series with R₃ = 4Ω, so the total resistance is\\( R_{eq} = 1.5 + 4 = 5.5Ω\\).</p>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "DC Circuits",
      "Equivalent Resistance"
    ]
  },
