    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 6 @ 2023/2024",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Which of the following is NOT an Ohmic conductor?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "metals",
        "aluminum wires",
        "nichrome wires",
        "solar cells"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "solar cells"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>Ohmic conductors follow Ohm's Law (V = IR) with a constant resistance. Metals and aluminum wires are Ohmic, while nichrome wires are typically Ohmic under certain conditions. Solar cells are non-Ohmic as their resistance varies with light intensity and voltage.</p>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "Electric Current",
      "DC Circuits",
      "Equivalent Resistance",
      "Ohm's Law"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 26 @ 2023/2024",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Three resistors R₁ = 10Ω, R₂ = 20Ω, and R₃ = 30Ω are connected in parallel. Find the equivalent resistance R_eq.",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "5.45 Ω",
        "0.183 Ω",
        "60 Ω",
        "17.5 Ω"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "5.45 Ω"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<div style='font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: 12px; border-radius: 6px; border-left: 4px solid #3498db;'>\n  <h3 style='margin-top: 0; color: #2c3e50;'>Step-by-Step Solution:</h3>\n  <ol>\n    <li><strong>Formula for Parallel Resistors</strong>:\n      <p>\\[ \\frac{1}{R_{eq}} = \\frac{1}{R_1} + \\frac{1}{R_2} + \\frac{1}{R_3} \\]</p>\n    </li>\n    <li><strong>Substitute Values</strong>:\n      <p>\\[ \\frac{1}{R_{eq}} = \\frac{1}{10} + \\frac{1}{20} + \\frac{1}{30} \\]</p>\n    </li>\n    <li><strong>Find Common Denominator (60)</strong>:\n      <p>\\[ \\frac{1}{R_{eq}} = \\frac{6}{60} + \\frac{3}{60} + \\frac{2}{60} = \\frac{11}{60} \\]</p>\n    </li>\n    <li><strong>Calculate R<sub>eq</sub></strong>:\n      <p>\\[ R_{eq} = \\frac{60}{11} \\approx 5.4545\\, \\Omega \\]</p>\n      <p><em>Rounded to 2 decimal places: <strong>5.45 Ω</strong></em></p>\n    </li>\n  </ol>\n  <p><strong>Key Note</strong>: The earlier answer (5.71 Ω) arose from rounding intermediate steps (e.g., 1/30 ≈ 0.0333). Using exact fractions avoids this error.</p>\n</div>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "DC Circuits",
      "Equivalent Resistance",
      "Resistors in Parallel"
    ]
  },
